source_content_norm: Local Flowers Care Instructions: 1. Clean your vase thoroughly. 2. Fill the vase two-thirds with fresh, lukewarm water. 3. Remove any leaves that will sit below the waterline. 4. You may notice some discolored outer petals. These are guard petals, which protect the inner petals. Gently remove 2-3 guard petals. 5. Trim about 2-3cm from the bottom of the stems at a 45-degree angle. 5. Keep your flowers out of direct sunlight, and in cool conditions (between 18 and 22 degrees Celsius). 6. Change the water regularly after the second day. 7. Remove any wilted flowers. 8. If after a few days, your roses start to droop, submerge the roses underwater and cut the stems again. Gently shake the stem to allow any air bubbles to escape. 9. Avoid placing fresh flowers near ripening fruit, as they can age the flowers prematurely. Note: Local flowers can last 2-3 days if the above care is followed and well maintained.
